/**
 * Computes the sign of the input number.
 *
 * @param {number} v - The number to compute the sign of.
 * @return {number} -1 if v < 0, 1 if v > 0, 0 otherwise.
 */
export const sign = (v) => (v < 0 ? -1 : v > 0 ? 1 : 0);

de:User:Venusianer / GNU FDL

64-bit float arithmetic for JavaScript. See [docs](https://arithmetic-type.github.io/double). Parent is [js-library](https://github.com/make-github-pseudonymous-again/js-library). ```js import {add, mul, sub, div} from '@arithmetic-type/double'; add(0.1, 0.2); // 0.30000000000000004 mul(0.1, 0.2); content:
# Installation

Can be managed using
[yarn](https://yarnpkg.com/en/docs),
[npm](https://docs.npmjs.com),
or [jspm](https://jspm.org/docs).


### yarn
```terminal
yarn add @arithmetic-type/double
```

### npm
```terminal
npm install @arithmetic-type/double --save
```

### jspm
```terminal
jspm install npm:@arithmetic-type/double
```
